####
# README - ccp data challenge
# Stuart Horsman (stuart.horsman@gmail.com)
###

Please read this to get started.  The data product contains the following
as requested by the submission procedure:

An abstract in PDF format that describes your approach to solving each of the 
three parts of the challenge. Please limit the length of the abstract to 
5 pages. -> found in ./docs/Abstract.pdf

Instructions for running your data product -> found in ./docs/Instructions.pdf

Any binary files for running your data product -> found in the ./bin directory

The three solution files called Task1Solution.csv, Task2Solution.csv, and 
Task3Solution.csv -> found in the ./output directory

The source files for your data product -> found in the ./src directory

###
# Mahout instructions
###
This describes how to compile Mahout, required for task3.

1) Get a copy of Mahout 0.8 and extract it into ~/ds-shorsman

2) cp ~/ds-shorsman/src/main/java/ccp/shorsman/mahout/PredictorEvaluator.java 
into ~/mahout/core/src/main/java/org/apache/mahout/cf/taste/hadoop/als

2) cp  ~/ds-shorsman/src/main/java/ccp/shorsman/mahout/*.props 
into ~/mahout/src/conf

3) cd ~/mahout; mvn clean install
